        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Cottonwood Valley, or 29 miles northwest of Limon, and
is stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Trail, Cottonwood Valley and Last Chance.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
